Defendant Robert J Koebler in court with attorney Jeffrey John Szczewski.  Ted Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews previous sentencing hearing. Parties are not able to give clarification regarding sentence credit. Court addresses bad WCS report. Defense will agree to State's offer of 72 day sentence credit. 

The Court Orders the Following: Count #6

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of 

6 months Jail (Credit - 72 days).  STAYED.

Term of Probation: 12 months

Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

No contact with Ryan Y.
Contact with mother and brother per agent's discretion.

AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s/drug screens;
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and disclose to your Agent all prescriptions. 

Maintain/Obtain part time employment;
Counseling to be determined by Agent.  

COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
